# Architecture Constraints (ADRs)

These decisions are fixed unless a new ADR supersedes them.

## Queue (ADR 001)

Use **ARQ + Redis** for all async work: ingestion, embeddings, AI analysis, email delivery, cron re-scraping.

```python
# ❌ BAD — blocking the request handler
@app.post("/ingest/run")
async def run_ingest(): await scrape_all_sources()

# ✅ GOOD — enqueue worker task
@app.post("/ingest/run")
async def run_ingest(): await redis.enqueue_job("ingest_jobs")
```

## AI layer (ADR 002)

Two phases: **ingestion** (embed jobs → pgvector) and **query** (embed CV → similarity search → LLM re-rank).

- Embeddings: `nomic-embed-text` (local) or `text-embedding-3-small` (API)
- LLM: `gemma3:4b` (local) or BYOK provider
- Retrieval targets the **job corpus**, not the CV

## Apply automation (ADR 003)

**No server-side browser automation** for applying. Surface direct links to original postings; user applies in their own browser. Hard cap: **10 relevant matches**.

## Job scraping (ADR 004)

Pluggable source interface. Official APIs (Adzuna, Jooble, Careerjet) are primary; **Apify** supplements Indeed/LinkedIn. API source wins over scraped duplicate. Sources are individually disable-able.
